\int_0^1 {\ln(1+x)\over x}\,dx
 \int^1_0 \frac{ \log (1+x) }{x} dx = \int^1_0 \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} (-1)^{n-1} \frac{x^{n-1}}{n} dx
 =\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} (-1)^{n-1} \int^1_0 \frac{x^{n-1} }{n} dx = \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} (-1)^{n-1}  \frac{1}{n^2}. 
\displaystyle S = \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{1}{n^2} = \frac{\pi^2}{6}.
\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} (-1)^{n-1}  \frac{1}{n^2} = S - 2\left( \frac{1}{2^2} + \frac{1}{4^2} + \frac{1}{6^2} + \cdots \right) = S - \frac{S}{2} = \frac{\pi^2}{12}.
\int^1_0 \frac{ \log (1+x) }{x} dx = \frac{\pi^2}{12}.
x = e^{-t}
 I = \int_0^1 \frac{\ln(1+x)}{x}\,dx = \int_0^\infty \ln(1+e^{-t})\,dt\,, 
 \ln(1 + e^{-t}) = \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{(-1)^{n-1}}{n}\,e^{-tn}\,, 
 I = \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{(-1)^{n-1}}{n}\,\int_0^\infty e^{-tn}\,dt = \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{(-1)^{n-1}}{n^2} = \frac{\pi^2}{12}\,. 
 \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{1}{n^2} = \frac{\pi^2}{6}\,? 
